      <h2>About the Project</h2>
      <div class="project">
        <p>
          This project demonstrates
          <span class="highlight">automated web deployment on AWS EC2</span>
          using <span class="highlight">Ansible</span>. It dynamically fetches
          the EC2 instance details <strong>Private IP Address</strong>,
          <strong>Availability Zone</strong>, and <strong>Hostname</strong>
          from the AWS Instance Metadata Service (IMDSv2) and displays them on a
          hosted web page.
        </p>
        <p>The deployment process involved:</p>
        <ul class="indented-paragraph">
          <li>Configuring EC2 with Ansible Playbook for automation</li>
          <li>Installing and starting Nginx automatically</li>
          <li>
            Using IMDSv2 token-based metadata retrieval for IP, Hostname & AZ
          </li>
          <li>
            Deploying a dynamic HTML template that renders real-time EC2 data
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="info">
          <h3>Live EC2 Instance Information</h3>
          <p class="indented-paragraph">
            <strong>Instance IP:</strong> <span id="ip"> {{ ec2_ip.stdout }}</span>
          </p>
          <p class="indented-paragraph">
            <strong>Availability Zone:</strong> <span id="az">{{ ec2_az.stdout }}</span>
          </p>
          <p class="indented-paragraph">
            <strong>Hostname:</strong> <span id="hostname">{{ ec2_hostname.stdout }}</span>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="explain">
          <p>
            This web page fetches EC2 metadata dynamically using JavaScript from
            the
            <strong>http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data</strong> endpoint.
            When hosted on an EC2 instance, these values update automatically to
            show real instance data.
